Key companies such as Pfizer, Bristol-Myers Squibb, and Merck & Co. Inc. are actively involved in the development of new treatments for NUT midline carcinoma, including targeted therapies and oral medications. The market is expected to be driven by the increasing focus on personalized medicine and the development of BET inhibitors for NMC.
